content.purpose: This script identifies and lists processes consuming more than 100 CPU units on a system.
security_analysis: Uses Invoke-Expression which can lead to code injection vulnerabilities if input is not properly sanitized
Uses ConvertTo-SecureString with plaintext key, which is not secure for production environments
content.parameters: This script does not use any parameters.
content.optimization: Consider adding error handling to manage potential exceptions when retrieving process information.

command_details.purpose: Retrieves a list of processes running on the local computer.
command_details.potential_risks: Minimal risk as it only reads process information.

command_details.purpose: Filters objects based on a specified condition, in this case, processes with CPU usage greater than 100.
command_details.potential_risks: No inherent risks, but ensure the condition is correctly specified to avoid incorrect filtering.

command_details.purpose: Selects specific properties of objects, here used to display only the Name and CPU properties.
command_details.potential_risks: Minimal risk as it only selects properties for display.
